Website - Bhuvan Corona 
Website URL - https://bhuvan-app3.nrsc.gov.in/corona/
Website Content Details -

data is only for the year 2020
 Bhuvan is an Indian geoportal developed by the National Remote Sensing Centre (NRSC) of the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO). It is a web-based platform that provides access to a wide range of geospatial data and services, including satellite imagery, maps, and GIS data.

Bhuvan Geoportal Corona is a specific application of Bhuvan that provides access to data and services related to the COVID-19 pandemic. The application includes data on the following topics:

Confirmed cases: This data shows the number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in each state, district, and city.

Active cases: This data shows the number of active COVID-19 cases in each state, district, and city.4
Recovered cases: This data shows the number of COVID-19 cases that have recovered in each state, district, and city.

Death cases: This data shows the number of COVID-19 deaths in each state, district, and city.

The application also provides access to a variety of maps and charts that visualize this data. These maps and charts can be used to track the spread of the pandemic and identify areas that are most affected.

Bhuvan Geoportal Corona is a valuable tool for government agencies, healthcare professionals, and the general public. It can be used to track the progress of the pandemic, identify areas that need assistance, and make informed decisions about public health.
